# Trivy Ignore File — Suppress false-positive vulnerability findings
# Each entry must include the vulnerability ID and a justification.
# Review periodically (quarterly) to check if Trivy's DB has been updated.

# CVE-2026-1260 (GHSA-38vq-g6vr-w8wf) — sentencepiece heap overflow
# Affects: sentencepiece < 0.2.1
# Status: FIXED in sentencepiece==0.2.1 (which we pin in requirements.txt)
# The v0.2.1 release notes explicitly state "Security fix to address a heap overflow issue".
# Trivy's vulnerability database may not yet reflect that 0.2.1 is the patched version.
# This is a confirmed false positive — our pinned version IS the fix.
CVE-2026-1260

# KSV118 — Helm Tiller deployed (Trivy misidentifies `fmd-distiller` as Tiller)
# Reason: pod name "fmd-distiller" contains the string "tiller"; there is no Helm Tiller
# running in this cluster. Suppress on all pod spec templates.
KSV118

# CVE-2025-69872 (GHSA-w8v5-vhqr-4h9v) — diskcache unsafe pickle deserialization
# Affects: diskcache <= 5.6.3 (workers/cache-service). 5.6.3 is the LATEST release
# and the advisory has NO fixed version, so there is no version to upgrade to.
# Status: NOT EXPLOITABLE in our usage. workers/cache-service/worker.py opens the
# cache with `disk=diskcache.JSONDisk`, so values are serialized/read as JSON and
# never unpickled — the vulnerable pickle code path is not exercised. The finding
# remains only because scanners match the package version (usage-blind), not the
# serializer in use. Re-evaluate (and drop this ignore) if a patched diskcache
# release ships. Full context at the pin in
# workers/cache-service/requirements-worker.txt.
CVE-2025-69872
